cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AR, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper describes a program logic for weak memory, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also deals with litmus tests, which are commonly used in computer architecture (cs.AR) to test the correctness of memory models. The stability rules mentioned in the paper suggest a focus on distributed systems (cs.DS), and the use of temporal modalities suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE).
